There can only be one President for each CEO. There can only be one CEO for each President.

The Chairperson of the Board of Directors will be known as the Ombudsman and will help resolve disputes between the President and the CEO.

The Board of Directors will be paid a bonus based on health, saftey, and environmental metrics, to be determined by GRC Vote. 

Owners will be paid for labor according to a wage chart to be negotiated with the CEO.

All products, especially software or computer programs intended for general use should include feedback for emission and sequestration of carbon dioxide.

Notes:

In the primary document the President is paid a bonus according to the company payroll and the CEO is paid a bonus based on the dividends they 
generate. It will be up to those parties to negotiate the balance between wages and dividends.

